Tmz Ode is written for an expected or imagined visit of Maecenas, on the first anniversary of the poet's narrow escape from the falling tree (2. 13. 2. 17. 27, 3. 4. 27). The festival of March 1 was the Matronalia. Maecenas is supposed on his entry to wonder what can be the reason that a bachelor's home shows preparation for sacrifice on such a day. The answer is, that the poet is paying a vow to Bac- chus, which he had made at the time of his miraculous preservation. ‘The best wine is to be brought out,’ and so the Ode passes into an invitation to Maecenas to enter into the spirit of the time—to forget the troubles of State. ‘All is going well 3 the Dacians are checked, the Parthians quarrelling among themselves, evenv
